{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "180587ff-7ce2-49f6-b797-ed120d812cad",
    "name": "NHS PDS - Technical Audit 2026",
    "description": "# **NHS PDS API Technical Audit 2026**\n\n## **Executive Summary**\n\nThis collection contains a comprehensive suite of automated tests for the **NHS Personal Demographics Service (PDS) FHIR API**. The primary objective is to validate the integrity of patient \"Golden Records\" through rigorous schema validation, security handshake audits, and functional regression.\n\n## **Key Testing Domains**\n\n- **Core Identity (Sprint 1):** Validation of Patient Resource retrieval via unique NHS Numbers.\n    \n- **Demographic Search (Sprint 2):** Verification of advanced search parameters (Family Name, Gender, Birthdate).\n    \n- **Security & Compliance:** Auditing OAuth 2.0 token integrity and error-handling protocols (4xx/5xx).\n    \n\n## **Technical Specifications**\n\n- **Environment:** NHS Digital Sandbox.\n    \n- **Standard:** HL7® FHIR® R4.\n    \n- **Requirement Mapping:** All requests are linked to Jira Requirement IDs (e.g., REQ-PDS-01).\n    \n\n## **Pre-requisites for Execution**\n\n1. Ensure the **\"NHS - Sandbox\"** environment is selected in the top-right corner.\n    \n2. Verify that `base_url` is pointing to the official NHS Sandbox endpoint.\n    \n3. Tokens are managed via the **Authorization** tab at the collection level to ensure inheritance across all requests.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "52118279",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/52118279-180587ff-7ce2-49f6-b797-ed120d812cad?source=collection_link"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Sprint 1 - Core Identity (Read)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "TC-PDS-01: Positive Validation: Successful Patient Record Retrieval",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Check for Success",
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200 OK\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Verify JSON Structure ",
                  "pm.test(\"Response contains the correct Patient ID\", function () {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.id).to.eql(pm.environment.get(\"nhs_number\"));",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response includes at least one name entry\", function () {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.name[0].family).to.not.be.undefined;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Check for official name (Clinical requirement)",
                  "pm.test(\"Response includes a valid name (official or usual)\", function () {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    var nameEntry = jsonData.name.find(n => n.use === 'official' || n.use === 'usual');",
                  "    ",
                  "    pm.expect(nameEntry).to.not.be.undefined;",
                  "    console.log(\"Validated name with type: \" + nameEntry.use);",
                  "});",
                  "// 1. Parse the JSON response",
                  "const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "// 2. Schema Consistency Check",
                  "pm.test(\"Schema Consistency: Response ID matches requested NHS Number\", function () {",
                  "    // This helper function looks for the variable regardless of where it is stored",
                  "    const requestedId = pm.variables.get(\"nhs_number\"); ",
                  "    ",
                  "    // Log to the Console (CMD+ALT+C) so we can see what Postman is finding",
                  "    console.log(\"Requested ID from Variable:\", requestedId);",
                  "    console.log(\"Actual ID from JSON Body:\", jsonData.id);",
                  "",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.id).to.eql(requestedId);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// 3. Header Check (ETag validation for caching/concurrency)",
                  "pm.test(\"Header Check: ETag is present for resource versioning\", function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('ETag')).to.not.be.undefined;",
                  "});",
                  ""
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/Patient/{{nhs_number}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "Patient",
                "{{nhs_number}}"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "TC-PDS-02: Negative Validation: Resource Not Found (404)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// 1. Status Code Validation",
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 404 Not Found\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(404);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// 2. Response Time Audit (Performance Benchmark)",
                  "pm.test(\"Response time is under 500ms for Resource-Not-Found\", function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(500);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// 3. FHIR Standard Error Handling (OperationOutcome)",
                  "pm.test(\"Response Body is a valid FHIR OperationOutcome\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.resourceType).to.equal(\"OperationOutcome\");",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.issue).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// 4. Diagnostic Clarity (Ensuring the error is useful for clinicians)",
                  "pm.test(\"OperationOutcome contains diagnostic error details\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const issue = jsonData.issue[0];",
                  "    ",
                  "    // Accept 'information' OR 'error' to align with Sandbox behavior",
                  "    pm.expect(issue.severity).to.be.oneOf([\"information\", \"error\"]);",
                  "    pm.expect(issue.code).to.be.oneOf([\"not-found\", \"processing\"]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// 5. Security Audit: Zero Information Leakage",
                  "pm.test(\"Error response does not leak sensitive PII or Stack Traces\", function () {",
                  "    const responseText = pm.response.text();",
                  "    // Ensure common sensitive keys or server tech tags aren't leaked in the error",
                  "    const sensitivePatterns = [/password/i, /stacktrace/i, /internal server/i, /admin/i];",
                  "    sensitivePatterns.forEach(pattern => {",
                  "        pm.expect(responseText).to.not.match(pattern);",
                  "    });",
                  "});",
                  ""
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/Patient/9999999999",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "Patient",
                "9999999999"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "TC-PDS-03: Security Validation: Unauthorized Access",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// 1. Validate Security Block (Status Code)",
                  "pm.test(\"Security: Access Denied (400 or 401)\", function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([400, 401]);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// 2. Validate No Sensitive Data Leaked",
                  "pm.test(\"Security: No Patient Data in Response\", function () {",
                  "    const responseBody = pm.response.text();",
                  "    pm.expect(responseBody).to.not.include(\"family\");",
                  "    pm.expect(responseBody).to.not.include(\"birthDate\");",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// 3. Validate Error Format (FHIR Standards)",
                  "pm.test(\"Schema: Response is a FHIR OperationOutcome\", function () {",
                  "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.resourceType).to.equal(\"OperationOutcome\");",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "apikey",
                "value": "WRONG_KEY",
                "type": "text",
                "disabled": true
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/Patient/{{nhs_number}}",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "Patient",
                "{{nhs_number}}"
              ]
            }
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
